  <text>
      <body>
       
         <head type="metadata"><name type="person" corresp="#HWB">Henry Ward Beecher</name> to <name type="person" corresp="#SLC">Samuel L. Clemens</name>
               <date when="1884-03-31">31 March 1884</date> &#x2022; <name type="place">Brooklyn, N. Y.</name>
               <sourceline>(MS: CU-MARK, UCLC 41855)</sourceline>
            </head>
         <div1  type="letter">
            <pb facs="beecherh001.jpg" xml:id="pb001" n="1"/>
               <opener>
                  <letterhead rend="right">henry ward beecher,<space extent="2"/>    
                     <lb/>brooklyn, n.y.</letterhead>
                  <dateline rend="indentdateline"><date when="1884-03-31">March 31, 1884</date></dateline>
                  <salute rend="text-indent:2">My dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Clements</salute>
               </opener>
               <p rend="text-indent:3">Although I am myself <add>a</add> very curmudgeon about answering autographe letters, yet, as usual with selfish people, I want <hi rend="italic">others</hi>'&#8212;and your reputation for kindness in this respect emboldens me to ask for a <hi rend="italic">double</hi> one, viz for real name &amp; pseudonym.</p>
               <closer>
                  <signed rend="indentsig"><name type="person"><hi rend="paraph">Henry Ward Beecher</hi></name></signed>
               </closer>
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="post-transmission">
               <pb facs="beecherh-env.jpg" xml:id="pb002" n="2"/>
               <div2 type="envelope">
               <ab>S. M. Clemen<add>t</add>s Esq | Hartford | Conn.</ab><!-- 's' written over 't', or smudged out, or is it part of letter text bleed-through? -->
               <ab><note type="ed" xml:id="ed001" place="inline">postmarked:</note> <hi rend="xs-smallcaps">new-york mar 31 2 30 pm 84</hi></ab>
               <ab><note type="ed" xml:id="ed002" place="inline">docketed by SLC, in pencil:</note> H W Beecher [<hi rend="italic">rule</hi>] | <del>mention</del> | use it</ab>
               </div2>
            </div1>
         <div1 xml:id="cm0001" type="commentary"/>
      </body>
